整个项目的最大挑战。由于限制车辆使用东涌道，本项目取得的许可证甚少。同时，因最接近工地的混凝土厂也需要超过一小时的车程，所以，每天混凝土的浇注量，只能限于200立方米。这限制对于工程的进度起了很大的影响。</p><br/><p>污水处理厂内的各座钢筋混凝土结构及建筑物，都呈不规则的形状。因此，虽耍采用特别设计的模板及复杂的临时支撜结构。这也为整个项目带来一定的难度。</p>','2025-06-03 03:25:26.609000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.665000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',13.00),(87,'znf3zsb80gmnshbowrrt5mcq','青衣第三及第八区地区休憩用地 (合约编号：SS L345)','青衣第三及第八区地区休憩用地','建筑署','2003 年 02 月 26 日 - 2004 年 06 月 24 日','<p>良好规划是本工程成功的关键，这项目中所种植的品种有些需在一些特定时间栽种，确保其可持续性。</p><br/><p>由于工地靠近民众，工地的安全及对环境影响是整个项目被关住的重点。以避免引起对居民生活不便。</p>','2025-06-03 03:26:11.404000','2025-07-07 07:18:32.263000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',14.00),(89,'v67jeztcs2lpp8qw48sp25sg','水边围及马田村防洪工程及新庆村和永宁围有关改善渠道工程 (合约编号：DC/2000/12)','水边围及马田村防洪工程及新庆村和永宁围有关改善渠道工程','渠务署','2001 年 12 月 20 日 - 2004 年 03 月 12 日','<p>工程內容主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在水边围及马田村建洪泛抽水站，并包括内部和外部装饰以及相关的蓄洪池</li><li>在水边围外围墙，包括围栏和闸口</li><li>在马田村建挡土墙，包括围栏和闸口</li><li>渠务工程，电缆管道及两个抽水站的泄水孔</li><li>水边围及马田村的园林绿化工程</li><li>在流浮山道十字路口排水管道和近屏山近新庆村建矩形排水渠道</li><li>其它上述项目的辅助工程</li><li>铺设永宁围附近的排水渠</li><li>铺设直径 1200毫米的双管式水道及相关的排水口和特殊沙井</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:27:14.360000','2025-07-07 07:18:32.428000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',15.00),(91,'dumsfjdsthb6iyclqer3mlz3','南昌站 (九广铁路 西铁合约编号CC-402)','南昌站','九广铁路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站作为西铁第一期的南面总站，是西铁及地铁东涌线的共享综合车站。车站的构造，不仅覆盖了现有的西九龙高架高速公路及机场快线、地铁东涌线，同时，也包括了相关的连接行车道路与高架桥梁系统。另外，在车站建设施工期间，要保持西九龙高架高速公路、机场快线及东涌线正常运作的要求，为施工带来了不少难度。因此，对施工的技术要求是非常高和严格的。</p><br/><p>本车站设有地面沿车轨站台，以及与地铁东涌线共用的地底车站大堂。该大堂建于正在营运中的机场铁路及东涌线的地底。为确保机场铁路及东涌线正常运作，所以特别选择以「从上而下」（top-down）的建筑方式兴建，其规模在香港实属罕见。地底车站大堂及站台设计配合地下空间进行最大限度的开发及利用，减少占用地面的空间，也确保外观的宏伟。在提供商业活动的同时，也利于乘客流向的疏导，凭借高效人流引导设计迅速将乘客引导至最近的机场快线车站、公共汽车站、住宅及商业区。</p><br/><p>为配合将来在车站顶棚会建筑多幢多层式的住宅物业及高层商业大厦，车站的梁、柱结构及其基础的设计作出了相应的预备工作，其基础包括多种不同类型的椿基：如大口径现浇钢筋混凝土搅拌椿、地下连续墙及打入式工字型钢椿等等。车站施工期间，在车站顶部预留了大楼底层的钢筋混凝土柱结构。将来上盖物业发展时，站顶平台会以平板多肢结构承托上盖的多层剪力墙，这对将来顶棚以上的楼宇设计时产生的任何变动，是一个弹性的处理方法。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 03:28:09.578000','2025-07-07 07:18:35.719000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',16.00),(93,'qv4j2fx1s58s5bwajiee9ppo','美孚站 (九广铁路 西铁合约编号CC-404)','美孚站','九广铁路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>美孚站位于荔枝角公园内，采用密封式设计。其设计特色在于使车站与公园环境融为一体。车站的天台设计为空中花园，其中包括园林绿化及各种休闲设施，为邻近的大型高密度住宅区如美孚新村及清丽苑等的居民提供服务。本站的整体设计及建造，均以融入相邻居民区与环境为主题。例如：提供足够的人行道及车道从车站通往邻近的住宅区等。在建筑期间减低对居民的影响，也是一个重要的事项。所以，在建筑期间，专门修建了一条临时人行天桥横跨整个工地，为居民提供方便的来往通道。工程完成后，由于西铁的通车，美孚站及其天台上的空中花园的建成启用，大幅改善了邻近地区的交通及环境，居民的生活质素也得到相应提高。</p>','2025-06-03 03:29:19.415000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.659000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',17.00),(95,'h1sl941ulix0gusfzm3ehrnv','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期 (合约编号：CV/98/01)','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期','土木工程署','1998 年 12 月 30 日 - 2002 年 05 月 17 日','<p>工程包括建造700米长的斜坡式防波海堤。管理位于沙田47B区的公众填土趸船转运站。收集公众填料。在白石角填海17公顷土地及进行相关的土质处理。建造单孔箱形暗渠，进行环境监察及绿化工程。</p>','2025-06-03 03:29:59.525000','2025-07-07 07:18:36.730000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',18.00),(97,'fwkv2mo5ew3l18pk17ibqfau','九龙观塘康宁道公园第一期建造工程 (合约编号：SS E362)','九龙观塘康宁道公园第一期建造工程','建筑署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>地盘平整工程包括大型挖掘约 60,000立方米，大约有 30％是岩层挖 掘。</li><li>建设长250米的护土墙，最高点为12米</li><li>在斜坡上兴建一条长130米的行车天桥。</li><li>兴建单幢式服务大楼（43mx12mx3.7m高）包括更衣室，厕所，售票 处，储藏室，办公室，急救室。职员室，机房，天井，憩坐处，小食亭 及通风廊。</li><li>外场工程包括围墙，网球场，游乐场，缓跑径，健身站，观景亭，泵房 和喷泉。</li><li>环境美化工程，停车场，公园家具，渠务和管道工程，机电工程，滤水 系统和水循环系统。</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:30:46.006000','2025-07-07 07:18:31.931000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',19.00),(99,'mvfaro5bjqob3e05ez3g5xol','荃湾七区城门路运动场建造工程 (合约编号：SS C410)','荃湾七区城门路运动场建造工程','建筑署','1995 年 01 月 01 日 - 1998 年 01 月 02 日','<p>建造两条有盖的观众看台以及相关的排水系统，水务设施，环境美化，机电工程和体育设施。</p>','2025-06-03 03:31:21.123000','2025-07-07 07:18:32.021000',NULL,8,36,'zh-CN',20.00),(101,'hot7fywc4xbikoddoxhgzkoo','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road (Contract No. HY/2003/27)','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 03:32:52.426000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.833000',NULL,8,36,'en',11.00),(103,'oommzl71mrn9cwxqdfw85om8','Construction of Cherry Street Park at Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon (Contract No. SS M327)','Construction of Cherry Street Park at Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','31 December 2003 - 01 August 2005','<p>The works included the construction of an open space park of a total site area of approx. 40,100m2. Extremely demanding  architectural features and high standard finishes were required for the project. </p>','2025-06-03 03:33:44.172000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.240000',NULL,8,36,'en',12.00),(105,'kwq8xba6pz0c078wbm01yktq','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p>','2025-06-03 03:34:43.390000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.963000',NULL,8,36,'en',13.00),(107,'nh7l5kb15g78fbje8ax3lkq8','Construction of District Open Space in Areas 3 & 8, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong (Contract No. SS L345)','Construction of District Open Space in Areas 3 & 8, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong','Architectural Services Department','26 February 2003 - 24 June 2004','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Strategic planning was one of the key to the success of this project as some of the vegetations can only be planted during certain time of the year to ensure their sustainability.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Due to the site&#x27;s proximity to the general public, the safety, environmental impact, access with minimal distraction and interruption to the local community and security were the main concerns throughout the project.</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:35:35.663000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.100000',NULL,8,36,'en',14.00),(109,'aa9hs89v59tsc7qlu806l88k','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:36:41.919000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.437000',NULL,8,36,'en',15.00),(111,'f7zubi517bc2qqczrad70ooo','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-03 03:38:08.503000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.407000',NULL,8,36,'en',16.00),(113,'qnefyaxl4m7p3s3mx21hikqa','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-03 03:38:56.941000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.778000',NULL,8,36,'en',17.00),(115,'xww87dzyryy34gbc1c8s27yk','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','<p>Works involved:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:39:53.891000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.291000',NULL,8,36,'en',18.00),(117,'ybeajg7j0rdy8j2t9l4u7kkx','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon (Contract No. SS E362)','Hong Ning Road Park Phase I at Kwun Tong, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','11 April 1997 - 26 March 1999','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The site formation includes a bulk excavation area of approximately 60,000m3. approximately 30% was rock excavation.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 250m long retaining walls with maximum height of 12m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a 130m-long carriageway bridge on a slope.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey service building (43mx12mx3.7m high) with changing rooms, toilets, booking office, storage room, general office, first aid room, staff room, plant rooms, open court, seating area, kiosk and breezeway.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>External works comprising barrier walls, tennis courts, play area, jogging tracks, fitness stations, pavilion, pump rooms and fountains.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works, car park, park furniture, drainage and plumbing works, M&amp;E works, water filtration and circulation installation.</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:40:48.538000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.224000',NULL,8,36,'en',19.00),(119,'h2ite9r1di4qctfy0gmcx7j4','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan (Contract No. SS C410)','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan','Architectural Services Department','01 January 1995 - 02 January 1998','<p>Construction of two covered spectator stands together with drainage and waterworks, landscaping, M&amp;E works and sports facilities. </p>','2025-06-03 03:40:48.989000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.238000',NULL,8,36,'en',20.00),(154,'oaosn2r7rima9j3clq5s3b2a','土木工程拓展署合约编号CV/2013/08 - 莲塘/香园围口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合约六','土木工程拓展署合约编号CV/2013/08 - 莲塘/香园围口岸土地平整及基建工程 – 工程合约六','土木工程拓展署','2015 年 06 月 24 日 - 2019 年 06 月 21 日','<p>莲塘/香园围口岸是香港、深圳之间第七个陆路口岸。现时文锦渡和沙头角两个陆路口岸，碍于地理限制，难有再扩建的空间。莲塘/香园围口岸位于文锦渡和沙头角之间，正好填补这个不足，使香港与广东省东部地区以至福建及江西的跨境交通连接更方便快捷。新口岸在策略上对推动长远经济发展十分重要。</p><p>兴建一条4.6公里的双程双线分隔主干道以连接沙头角公路交汇处及新口岸，提供排水/排污、水务及新口岸的公共设施工程，另外处理竹园村的迁移，相关的环境缓解措施，以及环境监测及稽核。</p>','2025-06-03 02:35:02.778000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.171000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.549000',8,36,'zh-CN',1.00),(155,'u7k104hyle1ml7q5064hw5xa','HK / 2012/08湾仔发展计划第二期–中环湾仔绕道湾仔西段','HK / 2012/08湾仔发展计划第二期–中环湾仔绕道湾仔西段','土木工程拓展署','2013 年 01 月 31 日 - 2018 年 11 月 28 日','<p>湾仔发展计划第二期为湾仔北和北角提供土地，被兴建中环及湾仔绕道和东区走廊连接路。纾缓湾仔附近一带的交通问题</p><p>本合约是一项超过5公里的大型填海工程。其地盘位由中环填海计划第三期东面海堤延伸至香港会议展览中心新翼的西边。其合约范围内的工程包括：挖泥工程，海提建造;水管接头;清拆博览道西桥，箱型渠延长，以及建造雨水渠务工程</p>','2025-06-03 02:35:43.269000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.172000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.555000',8,36,'zh-CN',2.00),(156,'p2gbj2yxa1udsv2jj9os8k2f','合约编号HY/2008/12屯门公路巴士转乘站','合约编号HY/2008/12屯门公路巴士转乘站','路政署','2010 年 07 月 15 日 - 2015 年 07 月 31 日','<p>该项工程主要包括在小榄交汇处附近的屯门公路往九龙方向及在大榄角回旋处附近的屯门公路往屯门方向辟设巴士转乘站，把兄弟桥扩阔，建造一条连接桥，可让乘客步行往来屯门公路及大榄角两个等候处转乘其他巴士线。连接桥上设有两部升降机，方便残障人士往来。另外进行附属工程，包括重建道路、建造上盖、渠务、环境美化、交通辅助设施、街道照明、斜坡、水务等工程及提供相关设施予交通管制监察系统。</p><p>这项工程旨在提供便利的巴士转乘设施，让乘客转乘取道屯门公路往来新界西北的各条巴士线。这项安排既能让现有乘客于转乘站有更多巴士路线的选择，又能大大提升新界西北巴士网络的整体效率，便利乘客，纾缓交通挤塞，以及减低路边空气污染。</p>','2025-06-03 02:37:52.326000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.173000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.560000',8,36,'zh-CN',4.00),(157,'pe5u6gqnriy2pozutvsko4yz','香港仔港湾兩岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街 一带之美化工程 (合约编号CV/2011/02)','香港仔港湾兩岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街 一带之美化工程','土木工程拓展署','2011 年 09 月 30 日 - 2014 年 12 月 31 日','<p>香港仔两岸海滨长廊和鸭脷洲大街一带之美化工程采用设计与建造合约形式。本工程主旨为改善香港仔两岸的旅游设施，进一步突显香港仔独有的&quot;传统渔港&quot;及本土文化特色，并加强多元化旅游的元素，以提升香港仔对海外旅客及本地居民的吸引力。</p>','2025-06-03 02:36:25.831000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.190000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.577000',8,36,'zh-CN',3.00),(158,'h6xmky3jzch6jk9laoovhqr0','屯门第18区L18A路道路工程 (合约编号：TM/2006/02)','屯门第18区L18A路道路工程','土木工程拓展署','2007 年 04 月 30 日 - 2009 年 05 月 29 日','<p>工程的主要项目包括建造一条长约 400米， 宽10.3米的双线行车道并两侧备有3.5米宽行人路; 及1段长约160米横跨皇珠路的高架桥并在桥两侧铺设长约 135米的挡土墙</p>','2025-06-03 02:41:49.221000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.364000','2025-07-07 07:18:30.654000',8,36,'zh-CN',8.00),(159,'gh8mj1ziep8icm6w5q5u7vhn','位于青衣及荃湾引道的青荃桥的隔音屏障加建工程 (合约编号: HY/2007/08)','位于青衣及荃湾引道的青荃桥的隔音屏障加建工程','路政署','2008 