路及东涌线的地底。为确保机场铁路及东涌线正常运作，所以特别选择以「从上而下」（top-down）的建筑方式兴建，其规模在香港实属罕见。地底车站大堂及站台设计配合地下空间进行最大限度的开发及利用，减少占用地面的空间，也确保外观的宏伟。在提供商业活动的同时，也利于乘客流向的疏导，凭借高效人流引导设计迅速将乘客引导至最近的机场快线车站、公共汽车站、住宅及商业区。</p><br/><p>为配合将来在车站顶棚会建筑多幢多层式的住宅物业及高层商业大厦，车站的梁、柱结构及其基础的设计作出了相应的预备工作，其基础包括多种不同类型的椿基：如大口径现浇钢筋混凝土搅拌椿、地下连续墙及打入式工字型钢椿等等。车站施工期间，在车站顶部预留了大楼底层的钢筋混凝土柱结构。将来上盖物业发展时，站顶平台会以平板多肢结构承托上盖的多层剪力墙，这对将来顶棚以上的楼宇设计时产生的任何变动，是一个弹性的处理方法。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 03:28:09.578000','2025-07-07 07:18:35.719000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.905000',8,36,'zh-CN',16.00),(175,'h1sl941ulix0gusfzm3ehrnv','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期 (合约编号：CV/98/01)','白石角公众卸泥填海，第三期','土木工程署','1998 年 12 月 30 日 - 2002 年 05 月 17 日','<p>工程包括建造700米长的斜坡式防波海堤。管理位于沙田47B区的公众填土趸船转运站。收集公众填料。在白石角填海17公顷土地及进行相关的土质处理。建造单孔箱形暗渠，进行环境监察及绿化工程。</p>','2025-06-03 03:29:59.525000','2025-07-07 07:18:36.730000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.911000',8,36,'zh-CN',18.00),(176,'ijdyuu4ndtptqvlze4nlqdud','美孚站 (九廣鐵路 西鐵合約編號CC-404)','美孚站','九廣鐵路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>美孚站位於荔枝角公園內，採用密封式設計。其設計特色在於使車站與公園環境融爲一體。車站的天台更被設計成爲空中花園。其中包括園林綠化及各種休憩設施。爲鄰近的大型高密度住宅屋村如美孚新村及清麗苑等的居民提供服務。本站的整體設計及建造，均以融合鄰近的民居及環境爲主題。例如：提供充足的行人及行車通道從車站接駁到鄰近的屋苑等。於建築期間，減低對居民的影響，也是一個重要的議題。所以，在建築期間，特別建造了一條臨時行人天橋橫跨整個工地，爲居民提供方便的來往通道。由於西鐵的通車，美孚站及其天台上的空中花園落成啓用，鄰近一帶地區的交通及環境得以大幅改善，居民的生活質素也相應提高。</p>','2025-06-03 03:17:13.231000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.801000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.989000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',17.00),(177,'uxafpuimilxvy4pwwd0nfz1z','南昌站 (九廣鐵路 西鐵合約編號CC-402)','南昌站','九廣鐵路','1999 年 10 月 01 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>南昌站是西鐵第一期的南面總站，爲西鐵及地鐵東涌線之共用綜合車站。車站的結構，不但覆蓋了現有之西九龍高架高速公路及機場快線、地鐵東涌線，同時，也包括了相關的連接行車道路與高架橋樑系統。在車站建設施工期間，西九龍高架高速公路，機場快線及東涌線要保持如常運作，這些要求，爲施工帶來了不少難度。因此，對施工的技術要求亦十分高和嚴格。</p><br/><p>本車站設有地面沿車軌月臺及與地鐵東涌線共用的地底車站大堂。該大堂建於正在營運中之機場鐵路及東涌線的地底。爲確保機場鐵路及東涌線如常運作，所以特別選擇以「從上而下」（top-down）的建築方式興建，其規模爲香港僅見。地底車站大堂及月臺設計配合地下空間的儘量開發及善用，減少地面空間的佔用，亦確保地面外觀宏偉吸引，同時提供商業活動之餘，亦方便乘客流向的疏導，以高效率設計迅速將人流導至相鄰的機鐵車站、公共汽車站、住宅及商業區。</p><br/><p>爲配合未來在車站上蓋將會發展多幢多層式的住宅物業及高層商業大廈，車站的梁、柱結構及其基礎的設計作出了相應的預備工夫，其基礎包括多種不同類型的椿基：如大口徑現澆鋼筋混凝土攪拌椿、地下連續牆及打入式工字形鋼椿等等。車站施工期間，於車站頂部預留大樓底層之鋼筋混凝土柱結構。將來上蓋物業發展時，站頂平臺會以平板多肢結構承托上蓋的多層剪力牆，對未來上蓋樓宇設計時可産生的任何變動，是一個保留彈性的處理方法。</p>','2025-06-03 03:16:31.034000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.828000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.005000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',16.00),(178,'qiifwf1y0ub2vm5cl140nr3v','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Contract No. HY/2008/12 Bus-Bus Interchanges on Tuen Mun Road','Highways Department','15 July 2010 - 31 July 2015','<p>The works mainly comprise the construction of a bus-bus interchange on Tuen Mun Road Kowloon-bound near Siu Lam Interchange and Tai Lam Kok roundabout, the widening of Brothers&#x27; Bridge, and the construction of a link bridge with two lifts. It will allow passengers to travel on foot from the holding area at TMR to the holding area at Tai Lam Kok to switch buses. Two lifts will be constructed in connection with the link bridge to provide access to people with disabilities. Its associated civil works include road reconstruction, provision of shelters, drainage, landscaping, traffic aids and street lighting, slope works, waterworks, and provisioning of works for traffic control surveillance.</p><p>The project aims at providing a convenient interchange facility for passengers to switch amongst bus routes from/to Northwest New Territories operating via Tuen Mun Road. This arrangement will not only provide passengers more choices of bus services at the bus-bus interchange, but also greatly enhance the overall efficiency of the bus network in the Northwest New Territories and reduce traffic congestion and road-side air pollution.</p>','2025-06-03 02:23:14.842000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.822000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.011000',8,36,'en',4.00),(179,'qv4j2fx1s58s5bwajiee9ppo','美孚站 (九广铁路 西铁合约编号CC-404)','美孚站','九广铁路公司','1999 年 08 月 02 日 - 2003 年 10 月 31 日','<p>美孚站位于荔枝角公园内，采用密封式设计。其设计特色在于使车站与公园环境融为一体。车站的天台设计为空中花园，其中包括园林绿化及各种休闲设施，为邻近的大型高密度住宅区如美孚新村及清丽苑等的居民提供服务。本站的整体设计及建造，均以融入相邻居民区与环境为主题。例如：提供足够的人行道及车道从车站通往邻近的住宅区等。在建筑期间减低对居民的影响，也是一个重要的事项。所以，在建筑期间，专门修建了一条临时人行天桥横跨整个工地，为居民提供方便的来往通道。工程完成后，由于西铁的通车，美孚站及其天台上的空中花园的建成启用，大幅改善了邻近地区的交通及环境，居民的生活质素也得到相应提高。</p>','2025-06-03 03:29:19.415000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.659000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.017000',8,36,'zh-CN',17.00),(180,'kwq8xba6pz0c078wbm01yktq','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline (Contract No. DC/2003/01)','Ngong Ping Sewage Treatment Plant, Trunk Sewers and Effluent Export Pipeline','Drainage Services Department','18 August 2003 - 09 March 2006','<p>Access to the site area was one of the challenging aspects of the project. The maximum daily fresh concrete delivery was restricted to 200 m3 due to the limited number of vehicular permits and the lengthy delivery time of at least one hour from the nearest concrete batching plant. This had a direct impact on the number of construction joints of the structure and the progress of the works.</p><br/><p>The irregular shapes of various reinforced concrete features of the Sewage Treatment Plant require special form work molds and complex false works arrangements.</p>','2025-06-03 03:34:43.390000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.963000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.199000',8,36,'en',13.00),(181,'u2paw6his0bfhxvnz7ncnjsj','昂坪汙水處理廠，污水幹渠及污水排放管道 (合約編號： DC/2003/01)','昂坪汙水處理廠，污水幹渠及污水排放管道','渠務署','2003 年 08 月 18 日 - 2006 年 03 月 09 日','<p>前往工地的通道一直爲整個專案的最大挑戰。由於限制車輛使用東涌道，本專案取得的許可證甚少。同時，因最接近工地的混凝土廠也需要超過一小時的車程，所以，每天混凝土的澆注量，只能限於200立方米。這限制對於工程的進度起了很大的影響。</p><br/><p>汙水處理廠內的各座鋼筋混凝土結構及建築物，都呈不規則的形狀。因此，雖耍採用特別設計的模板及複雜的臨時支撜結構。這也爲整個專案帶來一定的難度。</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 03:11:36.382000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.969000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.349000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',13.00),(182,'byqijjf8m60ilhd74ssgqawv','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun (Contract No.TM/2006/02)','Road L18A in AREA 18, Tuen Mun','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 April 2007 - 29 May 2009','<p>The major works in this project consisted of the construction of an approx. 400m long and 10.3m wide two-lane carriageway with a 3.5m wide footpath on both sides section of about 160m long elevated structure over Wong Chu Road was constructed with a total of about 135m of retaining wall structure at both ends of the elevated structure.</p>','2025-06-03 02:28:40.482000','2025-07-07 07:18:37.961000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.328000',8,36,'en',8.00),(183,'yq8b9hwnyabvcm45td3hd0fl','水邊圍及馬田村防洪工程及新慶村和永寧圍有關改善渠道工程 (合約編號：DC/2000/12)','水邊圍及馬田村防洪工程及新慶村和永寧圍有關改善渠道工程','渠務署','2001 年 12 月 20 日 - 2004 年 03 月 12 日','<p>工程主要包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在水邊圍及馬田村建洪氾抽水站，並包括內部和外部裝飾以及相關的蓄洪池</li><li>在水邊圍建邊界牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>在馬田村建擋土牆包括圍欄和閘口</li><li>渠務工程，電纜管道及兩個抽水站相關的拉線井</li><li>在水邊圍及馬田村的園林綠化工程</li><li>在流浮山道十字路口排水道和近屏山近新慶村建矩形排水渠道</li><li>其他上述項目的輔助工程</li><li>鋪設永寧圍附近的建築排水渠</li><li>鋪設直徑 1200毫米的雙管式水道及相關的排水口和特殊沙井</li></ul><br/>','2025-06-03 03:15:41.004000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.377000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.554000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',15.00),(184,'mg4uwpc42qy58z06w6m44usd','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area (Contract No. CV/2011/02)','Uplifting Works to Promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area','Civil Engineering and Development Department','30 September 2011 - 31 December 2014','<p>This is a Design and Build project for the uplifting works to promenades of Aberdeen Harbour and Ap Lei Chau Main Street Area. The objective of the works is to enhance the Aberdeen area and aim to further bring out the unique features of &#x27;traditional fishing harbour&#x27; and the local culture of Aberdeen and, by reinforcing the elements of diversified tourism, to enhance Aberdeen&#x27;s attractiveness to both international visitors and local residents.</p>','2025-06-03 02:22:33.929000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.409000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.578000',8,36,'en',3.00),(185,'aa9hs89v59tsc7qlu806l88k','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai (Contract No. DC/2000/12)','Village Flood Protection Works for Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen and RPIS Drainage Improvement Work at Sam Hing Tsuen and Wing Ning Wai','Drainage Services Department','20 December 2001 - 12 March 2004','<p>Major works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>The Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen Floodwater Pumping Station on raft foundation including internal and external finishes and their associated floodwater storage ponds</li><li>Boundary wall at Shui Pin Wai including fencing and gates</li><li>Retaining walls at Ma Tin Tsuen including fencing and gates</li><li>Drainage works, cable ducts and drawpits associated with the two pumping stations</li><li>Landscaping works at Shui Pin Wai and Ma Tin Tsuen</li><li>Cross road drain at Lau Fau Shan Road and rectangular drainage channels near San Hing Tsuen, Ping Shan</li><li>Other ancillary works associated with items above</li><li>Construction of drainage channels near Wing Ning Wai</li><li>Construction of the twin 1200mm diameter pipes and the associated outfall and special manhole</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:36:41.919000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.437000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.658000',8,36,'en',15.00),(186,'f7zubi517bc2qqczrad70ooo','Nam Cheong Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-402)','Nam Cheong Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','01 October 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Nam Cheong Station is the southern terminal of the West Rail. It is an interchange station for the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The structure envelopes the alignments of the existing elevated West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the existing Airport Express Line (AEL) and the MTR Tung Chung Line. It also includes the linking carriageway and the associated elevated flyover system. During the construction stage, the West Kowloon Expressway (WKE), the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line have to maintain normal operations. These requirements greatly increased the difficulties in the construction and required extremely high and stringent construction techniques.</p><br/><p>This station includes the track side platforms at ground level and an underground station hall for both the West Rail and the MTR Tung Chung Line. The underground station hall was constructed underneath the operating Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line. In order to ensure the operation of the Airport Express Line (AEL) and the Tung Chung Line, “Top down” construction method was employed. This kind of construction method on such a scale is seldom seen in Hong Kong.The underground station hall and platform design ensured the utilization and development of the underground space, and reduce occupied area at ground level. It also provided a grand outlook of the station. Apart from providing business activities, with the highly efficient pedestrian flow design, the crowds are quickly diverted to the relevant Airport Express Line station, bus station, residential blocks and commercial areas.</p><br/><p>The column, beam structure and foundation design of the station have made provisions for the future development of multi-storey residential blocks on top of the station. The foundations design includes large diameter cast in-situ concrete bored piles, diaphragm walls and driven steel H-piles, etc. Reinforced concrete column structures were reserved at the roof slab of the station for future construction of the multi-storey resident blocks. The multi-storey shear walls of the future superstructures will be supported by the transfer plate at the station roof. This accommodates any future change in the layout of the superstructure.</p>','2025-06-03 03:38:08.503000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.407000','2025-07-07 07:18:38.666000',8,36,'en',16.00),(187,'jftf41osq7xnpm5nbh2kj9vc','九龍大角咀興建櫻桃街公園 (合約編號：SS M327)','九龍大角咀興建櫻桃街公園','建築署','2003 年 12 月 31 日 - 2005 年 08 月 01 日','<p>興建約爲40, 100平方米的公園</p><p>主要工程包括：</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建造一個設有看臺的七人人造草地足球場</li><li>兩個可用作籃球場或排球場的場地</li><li>四個網球場</li><li>一條設有健身站的緩跑徑</li><li>一個種有