0,000m3. approximately 30% was rock excavation.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of 250m long retaining walls with maximum height of 12m.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a 130m-long carriageway bridge on a slope.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of a single storey service building (43mx12mx3.7m high) with changing rooms, toilets, booking office, storage room, general office, first aid room, staff room, plant rooms, open court, seating area, kiosk and breezeway.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>External works comprising barrier walls, tennis courts, play area, jogging tracks, fitness stations, pavilion, pump rooms and fountains.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works, car park, park furniture, drainage and plumbing works, M&amp;E works, water filtration and circulation installation.</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:40:48.538000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.224000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.421000',8,36,'en',19.00),(197,'m4c79oyn0a8to8yasw39wsnp','合約編號HY/2008/12屯門公路巴士轉乘站','合約編號HY/2008/12屯門公路巴士轉乘站','路政署','2010 年 07 月 15 日 - 2015 年 07 月 31 日','<p>該項工程主要包括在小欖交匯處附近的屯門公路往九龍方向及在大欖角迴旋處附近的屯門公路往屯門方向闢設巴士轉乘站，把兄弟橋擴闊，建造一條連接橋，可讓乘客步行往來屯門公路及大欖角兩個等候處轉乘其他巴士線。連接橋上設有兩部升降機，方便殘障人士往來。另外進行附屬工程，包括重建道路、建造上蓋、渠務、環境美化、交通輔助設施、街道照明、斜坡、水務等工程及提供相關設施予交通管制監察系統。</p><p>這項工程旨在提供便利的巴士轉乘設施，讓乘客轉乘取道屯門公路往來新界西北的各條巴士線。這項安排既能讓現有乘客於轉乘站有更多巴士路線的選擇，又能大大提升新界西北巴士網絡的整體效率，便利乘客，紓緩交通擠塞，以及減低路邊空氣污染。</p>','2025-06-03 02:47:36.948000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.246000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.435000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',4.00),(198,'p77813f2fsd219m8j1yj4yz3','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38 (Contract No. EP/SP/52/06)','Development of EcoPark in Tuen Mun Area 38','Environmental Protection Department','03 July 2006 - 01 January 2010','<p>The EcoPark is a key element of the strategy that aims to promote the local recycling industry and jump-start a sustainable economy by providing long-term land facility for the environmental and recycling industry. By encouraging and promoting the reuse, recovery and recycling of our waste resources and return them to the consumption loop, the EcoPark will help capitalize the potential of the local recycling industry and alleviate the heavy demand of the Hong Kong landfills.</p><br/><p>EcoPark occupies 20 hectares of land in Tuen Mun Area 38 and will be developed in two phases. Phase I of EcoPark (about 8 ha) will be available for occupation towards the end of 2006 and Phase II (about 12 ha) in 2009. Various environmentally friendly features are being used for the first time in Hong Kong, such as the Sun Pipe, Solar power water faucet, and a Green roof just to name a few.</p>','2025-06-03 02:31:08.569000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.256000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.471000',8,36,'en',9.00),(199,'xww87dzyryy34gbc1c8s27yk','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III (Contract No. CV/98/01)','Pak Shek Kok Reclamation for Public Filling, Stage III','Civil Engineering Department','30 December 1998 - 17 May 2002','<p>Works involved:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of about 700m sloping armoured seawall</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Management of a barging point at Sha Tin Area 47B</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Collection of public fill and reclamation of approx. 17 hectares of seabed at Pak Shek Kok and install prefabricated band drains</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of storm water drainage works including channels, a single cell and a 5 cells box culvert, carry out environmental monitoring and landscape work</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:39:53.891000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.291000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.566000',8,36,'en',18.00),(200,'h2ite9r1di4qctfy0gmcx7j4','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan (Contract No. SS C410)','Construction of a Sportsground at Shing Mun Road, Area 7, Tsuen Wan','Architectural Services Department','01 January 1995 - 02 January 1998','<p>Construction of two covered spectator stands together with drainage and waterworks, landscaping, M&amp;E works and sports facilities. </p>','2025-06-03 03:40:48.989000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.238000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.576000',8,36,'en',20.00),(201,'tq2oalawa8mm9banq15tkk51','觀塘綠化工程 (合約編號 CV/2009/06)','觀塘綠化工程','土木工程拓展署','2009 年 09 月 25 日 - 2011 年 03 月 24 日','<p>政府展開綠化總綱圖計劃的綠化工程，計劃是透過研究地區的位置和特性，為地區訂立適合的綠化大綱，並為規劃、設計和推行有關工程提供指引。除了提供建議的種植地點外，綠化總綱圖亦會確立綠化主題，及建議適合的栽種主題和植物品種，以取得持續和一致的綠化效果。</p><p>集團於2009年獲得當中的觀塘綠化工程合約。工程主要包括在觀塘區內種植及培植約2,940棵樹木及840,000棵灌木和相關景觀設施，包括花槽，灌溉設施和相關的路面工程。</p>','2025-06-03 02:49:50.352000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.519000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.723000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',5.00),(202,'d6j9k8oy0ml91sdu91x034hu','屯門第38區環保園發展工程 (合約編號：EP/SP/52/06)','屯門第38區環保園發展工程','環境保護署','2006 年 07 月 03 日 - 2010 年 01 月 01 日','<p>環保園是一個關鍵因素的戰略，其目的是促進本地循環再造業和快速啟動一個可持續發展的經濟提供長期的土地設施的環境及循環再造業。通過鼓勵和促進再利用，回收和循環再造的廢物資源，並返回他們的消費循環中，環保園將有助於利用的潛力本地循環再造業，減輕沉重的需求，香港的堆填區。</p><br/><p>環保園佔地 20公頃的土地位於屯門第38區，將分兩個階段發展。環保園第一期（約 8公頃），將用於對結束佔領和2006年第二期（約 12公頃）在2009年。各種環保設施正在使用首次在香港，如太陽管道，太陽能水龍頭，並且有綠色屋頂等等</p>','2025-06-03 02:55:32.658000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.478000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.797000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',9.00),(203,'oy1wjboy6l73zrzbo63k16wt','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程 (合約編號：SS E362)','九龍觀塘康寧道公園第一期建造工程','建築署','1997 年 04 月 11 日 - 1999 年 03 月 26 日','<ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>地盤平整工程包括大型挖掘約 60,000立方米，大約有 30％是岩層挖 掘。</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>建設長250米的護土牆，最高點為12米</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>在斜坡上興建一條長130米的行車天橋。</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>興建單幢式服務大樓（43mx12mx3.7m高）包括更衣室，廁所，售票 處，儲藏室，辦公室，急救室。職員室，機房，天井，憩坐處，小食亭 及通風廊。</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>外場工程包括圍牆，網球場，遊樂場，緩跑徑，健身站，觀景亭，泵房 和噴泉。</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>環境美化工程，停車場，公園家具，渠務和管道工程，機電工程，濾水 系統和水循環系統。</li></ul>','2025-06-03 03:18:52.238000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.618000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.903000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',19.00),(204,'zo9ves6l86lc3lhavonc939f','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Contract No. HK/2012/08 – Wan Chai Development Phase II – Central – Wan Chai Bypass at Wan Chai West','Civil Engineering and Development Department','31 January 2013 - 28 November 2018','<p>The key purpose of Wan Chai Development Phase II is to provide land at Wan Chai North and North Point for the construction of the Central - Wan Chai Bypass and Island Eastern Corridor Link. Land formed under the project will be developed as a world-class waterfront promenade for public enjoyment and solve the traffic problem around Wan Chai district.</p><p>This is one of the contract in Wan Chai Development Phase II. It is a large scale Reclamation Project with more than 5 Ha. in size. The Project&#x27;s location is from the Central Reclamation Phase III (CRIII) eastern seawall to the west of Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Centre Extension. The scope of work includes dredging works, seawall works, watermains laying, demolition of existing Expo Drive West Bridge, box culvert extension and stormwater drainage works.</p>','2025-06-03 02:21:17.704000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.769000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.971000',8,36,'en',2.00),(205,'qnefyaxl4m7p3s3mx21hikqa','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>','2025-06-03 03:38:56.941000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.778000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.041000',8,36,'en',17.00),(206,'hot7fywc4xbikoddoxhgzkoo','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road (Contract No. HY/2003/27)','Reconstruction of Causeway Bay Flyover and Associated Widening of Victoria Park Road','Highways Department','10 June 2004 - 29 May 2008','<p>One of the most complex and challenging aspects of this project is the temporary traffic arrangements (TTA) while constructing the flyover in the highly congested area of Causeway Bay.</p><br/><p>Numerous traffic simulations analyses are required to study the impact of each TTA scenario. The analyses requires tremendous amount of data to accurately predict the effects of any chosen TTA.</p><br/><p>A 70m long temporary steel off ramp was constructed to maintain the existing traffic flow, with part of the existing flyover initially demolished to allow the construction of the proposed flyover.</p><br/><p>The low soffit level of the proposed flyover with gradients in both directions and the road height clearance requirement coupled with the excessively long span over Victoria Park Road made the design of the falsework decking nearly impossible. The depth of the deck had to meet the various road height clearances, and structural requirements.</p><br/><br/>','2025-06-03 03:32:52.426000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.833000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.060000',8,36,'en',11.00),(207,'g4tfyhygp8lrsgfkbjmuj65x','青衣第3及第8區地區休憩用地 (合約編號：SS L345)','青衣第3及第8區地區休憩用地','建築署','2003 年 02 月 26 日 - 2004 年 06 月 24 日','<p>良好規劃是本工程成功的關鍵，這項目中所種植的品種有些需在一些特定時間栽種，確保其可持續性。</p><br/><p>由於地盤靠近民眾，地盤的安全及對環境影響是整個項目被關住的重點。以避免引起對居民生活不便。</p>','2025-06-03 03:13:51.169000','2025-07-07 07:18:39.876000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.116000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK',14.00),(208,'hnbi1ru1ycy3cghoq1bub0cx','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches (Contract No. HY/2007/08)','Retrofitting of Noise Barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridge at Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches','Highways Department','08 January 2008 - 09 July 2011','<p>The major elements of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of noise barriers on Tsing Tsuen Bridgeat Tsing Yi and Tsuen Wan Approaches</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated structural modification works to existing bridge parapet and utility troughs</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Associated civil, geotechnical traffic aids, road pavement, drainage etc.</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Utilities diversion</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Landscaping works</li></ul>','2025-06-03 02:26:52.736000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.013000','2025-07-07 07:18:40.192000',8,36,'en',7.00),(209,'okm6jgyigy8207rat8xvmoz1','荃灣七區城門路運動場建造工程 (合約編號：SS C410)','荃灣七區城門路運動場建造工程','建築署','1995 年 01 月 01 日 - 1998 年 01 月 02 日','<p>建造兩座有蓋觀眾看臺以及相關之排水系統，水務設施，環